What is Agentic AI?

Agentic AI refers to AI systems that can act autonomously to achieve a goal by making decisions, planning steps, and taking actions without constant human intervention.

Unlike normal Generative AI (which only responds to prompts), Agentic AI can:

Set sub-goals

Plan steps

Use tools (APIs, databases, browsers)

Make decisions based on feedback

Retry if something fails

ğŸ§  Simple Difference
Generative AI	Agentic AI
Responds to prompt	Takes actions toward a goal
One-step output	Multi-step reasoning
No memory of tasks	Can maintain context & memory
Example: Write an email	Example: Plan and book a trip
